{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-jsx","path":"/react/scheduler/docs/guides/fundamentals/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"react-scheduler---fundamentals\"><a href=\"#react-scheduler---fundamentals\" aria-label=\"react scheduler   fundamentals permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>React Scheduler - Fundamentals</h1>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://devexpress.github.io/devextreme-reactive/react/scheduler\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">DevExtreme React Scheduler</a> is a component that displays appointments in different layouts. It also allows a user to <a href=\"./editing.md\">edit</a> appointments. You can enable each of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Create,_read,_update_and_delete\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">CRUD</a> operations separately.</p>\n<p>The Scheduler's UI elements include <a href=\"../reference/date-navigator.md\">date navigator</a>, <a href=\"../reference/view-switcher.md\">view switcher</a>, <a href=\"../reference/all-day-panel.md\">all-day panel</a>, <a href=\"../reference/appointment-tooltip.md\">appointment tooltip</a>, <a href=\"../reference/appointment-form.md\">appointment form</a>, and others. The following image illustrates these elements:</p>\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 776px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/devextreme-reactive/static/2fb622b9ed54b3c30d2c7eb37a81c1a3/167b5/scheduler-elements.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 50.256410256410255%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"scheduler elements\" title=\"scheduler elements\" src=\"/devextreme-reactive/static/2fb622b9ed54b3c30d2c7eb37a81c1a3/167b5/scheduler-elements.png\" srcset=\"/devextreme-reactive/static/2fb622b9ed54b3c30d2c7eb37a81c1a3/cb9a0/scheduler-elements.png 195w,\n/devextreme-reactive/static/2fb622b9ed54b3c30d2c7eb37a81c1a3/727ba/scheduler-elements.png 390w,\n/devextreme-reactive/static/2fb622b9ed54b3c30d2c7eb37a81c1a3/167b5/scheduler-elements.png 776w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 776px) 100vw, 776px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</p>\n<p>The Scheduler adheres to the plugin-based architecture: every feature is encapsulated in a dedicated plugin (or React component).</p>\n<h2 id=\"basic-setup\"><a href=\"#basic-setup\" aria-label=\"basic setup permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basic Setup</h2>\n<p>The Scheduler displays data specified via the <code class=\"language-text\">data</code> property. Data objects should have the same structure as the <a href=\"../reference/scheduler.md/#appointmentmodel\">AppointmentModel</a>. You can also <a href=\"https://github.com/DevExpress/devextreme-reactive/blob/master/packages/dx-react-scheduler-demos/src/demo-sources/scheduler-featured-remote-data/material-ui/demo.jsx#L53\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">extend the objects with custom fields</a>.</p>\n<p>The Scheduler requires the following plugins for basic data visualization:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One of the <a href=\"../reference/day-view.md\">DayView</a> / <a href=\"../reference/week-view.md\">WeekView</a> / <a href=\"../reference/month-view.md\">MonthView</a> - each of them renders a specific appointment layout.</li>\n<li><a href=\"../reference/appointments.md\">Appointments</a> - renders appointments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To specify the date that should be initially displayed in the date navigator and used for calculations, use the <a href=\"../reference/view-state.md\">ViewState</a> plugin's <code class=\"language-text\">currentDate</code> option. Otherwise, the widget uses current date.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-basic/basic-setup\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<h2 id=\"customize-the-appearance\"><a href=\"#customize-the-appearance\" aria-label=\"customize the appearance permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Customize the Appearance</h2>\n<p>The Scheduler's visualization plugins provide an API that allows you to customize the appearance of the UI elements.</p>\n<p>For example, the <code class=\"language-text\">WeekView</code> plugin provides <a href=\"../reference/week-view.md/#properties\">properties</a> that you should specify to customize the layout's appearance. The following sample demonstrates how you can implement the <code class=\"language-text\">timeTableCellComponent</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">dayScaleCellComponent</code> to highlight current date and weekends. You can use the same approach with any other UI plugin.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-basic/custom-template\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>","fields":{"technology":"react/scheduler","section":"docs"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"react/scheduler/docs/guides/fundamentals/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3159585216","3662068265"]}